# **Part 2**

## **Describe a person you know who loves to grow plants.**

One person I know who really loves growing plants is my grandmother. Ever since I was a child, she has always been interested in gardening and taking care of different kinds of plants. Although she’s already retired, she spends a lot of time looking after her small garden and seems to genuinely enjoy the process.

She mainly grows vegetables and flowers. For example, during spring and summer, she often grows tomatoes, cucumbers, peppers, and green onions. Besides vegetables, she also plants flowers like roses and chrysanthemums because she thinks they make the environment feel more relaxing and lively. What surprises me most is that she seems to know a lot about plants, such as when they should be watered, how much sunlight they need, and even how to deal with insects naturally.

Most of the plants are grown in a small yard beside her house, although she also keeps some smaller plants on the balcony. Whenever I visit her, I usually see her watering plants, trimming leaves, or checking whether the vegetables are growing properly. In a way, gardening has almost become part of her daily routine.

I think she enjoys growing plants for several reasons. First of all, it gives her a sense of peace and relaxation. Instead of spending all day indoors, she can stay active and spend time in nature. Secondly, she feels proud when the vegetables she grows are healthy and fresh because she knows exactly how they were produced. Personally, I really admire her patience because taking care of plants requires consistency and responsibility. Watching her also made me realise that gardening is not just about growing food or flowers, but also about enjoying a slower and healthier lifestyle.

---

## **中文翻译：**

我认识的一个非常喜欢种植物的人是我的奶奶。从我小时候开始，她就一直很喜欢园艺和照顾植物。虽然她已经退休了，但仍然花很多时间打理自己的小花园，而且她似乎真的很享受这个过程。

她主要种蔬菜和花。比如春夏季节，她经常种西红柿、黄瓜、辣椒和小葱。除了蔬菜，她也会种玫瑰和菊花，因为她觉得这些花能让环境更轻松、更有生气。最让我惊讶的是，她懂很多植物知识，比如什么时候浇水、需要多少阳光，甚至知道怎么自然防虫。

大部分植物种在她家旁边的小院子里，另外阳台上也会放一些小盆栽。每次我去看她时，经常能看到她在浇水、修剪叶子，或者检查蔬菜长得怎么样。从某种程度上来说，园艺已经成了她日常生活的一部分。

我觉得她喜欢种植物有几个原因。首先，这能让她感到平静和放松。相比一直待在室内，她可以活动身体并接触自然。其次，当看到自己种出来的蔬菜健康又新鲜时，她会特别有成就感，因为她清楚这些食物是怎么种出来的。我非常佩服她的耐心，因为照顾植物需要长期坚持和责任感。看着她，我也意识到园艺不仅仅是种花种菜，更是一种更慢、更健康的生活方式。

