## **1. What are the advantages of growing vegetables or flowers at home?**

I think there are quite a few advantages. First of all, growing vegetables at home can provide fresher and healthier food because people know exactly how the plants are grown and whether chemicals are used. Secondly, gardening can help people relax mentally. Nowadays many people live stressful and fast-paced lives, so taking care of plants can be a peaceful activity. In addition, flowers and plants can improve the living environment by making homes look more natural and pleasant. So overall, I think growing plants is beneficial both physically and emotionally.

### **中文：**

我觉得好处有很多。首先，在家种蔬菜能吃到更新鲜、更健康的食物，因为人们知道这些植物是怎么种的。其次，园艺还能帮助人放松。现在很多人的生活节奏很快，而照顾植物是一件很平静的事情。另外，花草还能让家里环境更自然、更舒服。所以我觉得种植物对身体和心理都有好处。

---

## **2. Do many people grow vegetables or flowers at home in your country?**

Yes, especially older people. In China, many retired people enjoy growing vegetables or flowers because they have more free time and see gardening as a relaxing hobby. In rural areas, it’s quite common for families to grow vegetables in their own yards. Even in cities, some people keep small plants or flowers on balconies because they want to make their homes feel greener and more comfortable. I think interest in gardening has gradually increased in recent years as people pay more attention to healthy lifestyles.

### **中文：**

是的，尤其是老年人。在中国，很多退休的人喜欢种花种菜，因为他们有更多时间，也把园艺当成一种放松方式。在农村，家家户户种菜非常普遍。即使在城市，也有很多人会在阳台种花草，因为他们想让家里更有自然感。我觉得随着人们越来越重视健康生活，近几年大家对园艺的兴趣也变大了。

---

## **3. Is it easy to grow plants at home?**

I think it depends on the type of plant and the environment people live in. Some plants are relatively easy to take care of and don’t require much experience, while others can be quite difficult because they need specific temperatures, sunlight, or watering schedules. In addition, people living in apartments may have limited space compared with those living in houses with gardens. However, nowadays there’s a lot of information online, so beginners can learn gardening skills more easily than before.

### **中文：**

我觉得这取决于植物种类以及居住环境。有些植物很好养，不需要太多经验；但有些则比较难，因为它们对温度、阳光和浇水要求很高。另外，住公寓的人空间可能有限，不像有院子的房子。不过现在网上有很多教程，所以新手比以前更容易学习园艺。

---

## **4. Why do some people prefer to grow their own fruits and vegetables instead of buying them from the market?**

I think one major reason is health and food safety. When people grow vegetables themselves, they feel more confident about the quality because they know exactly what has been used during the growing process. Another reason is that home-grown fruits and vegetables are often fresher and may even taste better. Besides practical reasons, many people also simply enjoy the experience of gardening because it gives them a sense of achievement. Watching something grow from a small seed into food can be surprisingly satisfying.

### **中文：**

我觉得一个主要原因是健康和食品安全。自己种菜的人会更放心，因为他们知道种植过程中用了什么。另外，自己种的水果和蔬菜通常更新鲜，味道也可能更好。除了这些实际原因之外，很多人也单纯享受种植过程，因为它会带来成就感。看着植物从种子慢慢长大，其实是一件很有满足感的事情。
